1. Open the battery compartment;
2. Verify the marking (label or molded inside the compartment);
3. Insert the batteries according to the marking and test the product function;
4. Battery cover: the cover should fit, stay closed securely and protect efficiently the battery.

1. To make sure the surface is clean before the test.
2. Use a strip of pressure-sensitive tape (3M 500 for instance) and apply it firmly on the whole area to be tested: artwork, logo, marking or the area specified by the client;
3. Press it by hand on the surface so that the tape is properly stuck, with no bubble or wrinkle;
4. Remove the tape in 0.5-1s with an angle close to 60 degrees, rapidly but not jerked.
5. Repeat this operation 3 times in the same area, the used tape should be cut off.

1. Open the product;

2. Check the cables status and protection, wire stops;

3. Check the internal reliability of the product design, verifying the the components are solidly held in place, and looking for any loose part;

4. Check the quality of wire soldering: use the normal force to pull the internal wire to verify it is well secured.

Take pictures to showing the whole internal construction, and any noteworthy details and issue found.
